<title>JAPAN: Hikari Tsushin cancels warrant bond issue.</title>
<headline>Hikari Tsushin cancels warrant bond issue.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-05-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Hikari Tsushin Inc said on Thursday that it had decided to cancel a planned issue of 490 million yen worth of domestic warrant bonds.</p>
<p>The proposed terms of the issue were announced earlier this month.</p>
<p>The telecommunications subscription agency said the decision was due to sharp movements in its stocks after it set the terms of the bonds, and the price surged far above the warrants' exercise price of 8,096 yen.</p>
